The DSS asked Nigerians to disregard other channels, as they were fake. Nigerian spy police, the Department of State Services (DSS) has created and released its social media handles saying they would be used to engage the Nigerian public. In a terse statement on Monday, the DSS asked Nigerians to disregard other channels, as they were fake. “The Department of State Services (DSS) hereby informs the public that it has created Social Media handles which are as follows: Twitter:@OfficialDSSNG Facebook: OfficialDSSNG and Instagram: @OfficialDSSNG. “Similarly, the PRO’s Twitter handle is @DrAfunanya_PNA. Hitherto, the Service did not own or operate these handles. Its decision to operate them with effect from 6th March, 2023 is to enhance public and stakeholder engagements. “The public should be guided and NOTE that any such handles before now were/are FAKE, please,” a statement by Peter Afunanya, said on Monday.